==English==
===Etymology===
From prefix ''[[dis-]]'', '''not''', + ''[[mount]]''

===Noun===

# In [[gymnastics]], the part of a routine in which the gymnast detaches from an apparatus.
#: "A stylish routine, let down by a sloppy dismount."

===Verb===
'''dismount''', '''[[dismounting]]''', '''[[dismounted]]'''

# [[get off]] (from a horse), get down from (a horse)
#: "She carefully dismounted from the horse."

